                        <td height="63"><img src="../global/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="1"> 
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">Borg ya Borg ya Borg ya like a Swedish Chef</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/7.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=62"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=62"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=2451">Jake "NeDraco" Rich</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>It is about the Borg and the Alpha Quadrant.</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>The main basis of this article is to pass information on to Borg players, or people<br>
that may play Borg in the future, on how the Voyager set will affect them. Experienced<br>
Borg players may find that this will contain information that they will find useless.(You<br>
have been warned) So if you are one of those people don&amp;#8217;t review this low just because<br>
you know all about it because it is ment for less experienced players.<br>
<br>
	What does the Alpha quadrant mean for the Borg. Oh no now if you want to play<br>
Borg you have to seed your Outpost at a Alpha quadrant mission. This also means that<br>
your opponent can have easy access to your Outpost making it available for destruction.<br>
This is something that every Borg player is going to have to fear now, Armada decks. But<br>
it is really not as bad as it may seem considering that they are relatively slow and you<br>
should have a fully staffed cube to report you drones on in the event that they do destroy<br>
you Outpost. <br>
<br>
	Unfortunately the Borg are not alone in the Alpha quadrant, they have three races<br>
to deal with, The Kazon,  The Vidians, and the small amount  of Feds they might<br>
encounter. The Kazon pose the most threat with their huge ships that work just like a cube<br>
and the fact that they cannot be assimilated when the The Kazon Collective is out. The<br>
Vidians can take hard hits at the Borg too. For instance lets view the Borg as a buffet bar<br>
and the Vidians as a 450 pound gorilla that just escaped from a science lab that was<br>
depriving it of food for weeks on end. Now there is not much you can do to stop those<br>
Vidians from sucking your Borgs organs out. First off they are not &amp;#8220;killed&amp;#8221; but &amp;#8220;victims&amp;#8221;<br>
so they can&amp;#8217;t be reabsorbed. Also they aren&amp;#8217;t attacking you so you can&amp;#8217;t attack back.<br>
Sucks huh? <br>
<br>
	Well there are several ways to combat both species from beating up on you. Run<br>
several Assimilate Counterparts and 6-8 Assault drones. Fight them back, I have found<br>
that my opponents become very distressed when the normally passive Borg start<br>
rampaging. Also include Adapt: Remodulate Shields to stop their phasers and disrupters.<br>
For space battles against the Kazon start running two cubes with Multiplexor drones and a<br>
Queen on one and a Counterpart  on the other. that way IF they do manage to destroy one<br>
of you cubes they will lose all of their ships in the battle and then you play Three<br>
Dimensional Thinking to relocate all the crew to the other cube. So you lost a cube and<br>
they lost more ships but managed to get 45 points and just made them selves easy targets<br>
for that other cube. Staffing two cubes just got easier with Delta Quadrant Spacial<br>
Scission(more later)<br>
<br>
	Playing all Alpha quadrant missions is a huge advantage to the Borg. They now no<br>
longer have to worry about having their Transwarp Network Gateway revolved and then<br>
have to get a AU doorway. One instance I had that happen to me and I didn&amp;#8217;t have the AU<br>
doorway  so I got to sit there and watch my opponent kick my butt cause I couldn&amp;#8217;t do<br>
anything. They also have the advantage of being able to start in the middle of the space<br>
line instead of on either end which can be harsh if you key mission are in the middle.<br>
<br>
	Delta Quadrant Spacial Scission is the best card for the Borg in the entire set,<br>
TWO Seven of Nines(staffing multiple cube just got easier) two Third of Five( eh why<br>
not?) and the best two of the some Counterparts, ever had one captured and then you<br>
can&amp;#8217;t play another one because you don&amp;#8217;t have He Will Make An Excellent Drone. Well if<br>
they do capture on just slap down another on and you have lost nothing.<br>
<br>
	Granted there are probably more cards that are going to be tech for borg players<br>
but the are the cards and strategies that I have found will be the most useful. So I hope<br>
you have enjoyed and I can&amp;#8217;t wait to test out my new Borg deck which should be pretty<br>
interesting. If you have any questions please D-mail me and I&amp;#8217;ll answer them.<br>
<br>
We Are Watching </span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=62"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=62"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="/stccg/global/images/back.gif" border="0" ></a></TD><TD><a href="articleprint.php3?article=62" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="/stccg/global/images/print.gif" border="0"></a></TD></TR></TABLE>
